From b5effb7d8d70b5c0cb3c4ed98ac11a4687fc893f Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: "LU, Xinbo" <luxinbo4@huawei.com>
Date: Thu, 26 Mar 2026 21:09:11 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] Problem: Configuring
 `PCP.Client.{i}.Server.{i}.InboundMapping.{i}.ThirdPartyAddress` with IPv6
 address has no effect

Cause: In the `add_map` function, during validation of the input parameter `thirdparty_addr`, the incorrect variable `rv` is used to check the value returned in `pton_rv`. This causes the configuration to fail with bad address error.

Solution: Correct variable name in address conversion check.

Issue: PPW-1681 `PCP.Client.{i}.Server.{i}.InboundMapping.{i}.ThirdPartyAddress` Not Applied Due to Validation Error [fix]
---
 mod-pcp-libpcp/src/mod_pcp.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/mod-pcp-libpcp/src/mod_pcp.c b/mod-pcp-libpcp/src/mod_pcp.c
index d98772a..6af796d 100644
--- a/mod-pcp-libpcp/src/mod_pcp.c
+++ b/mod-pcp-libpcp/src/mod_pcp.c
@@ -237,7 +237,7 @@ static bool add_map(server_t* s, map_t* m, amxc_var_t* args) {
         memset(&sa, 0, sizeof(struct sockaddr_storage));
 
         pton_rv = inet_pton(AF_INET6, thirdparty_addr, &psa6->sin6_addr);
-        if(rv == 1) {
+        if(pton_rv == 1) {
             sa.ss_family = AF_INET6;
         } else {
             pton_rv = inet_pton(AF_INET, thirdparty_addr, &psa->sin_addr);
-- 
